{"questionId":"22651845","questionHtml":"<p>State the null and alternative hypotheses for the test.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>μ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></msub></math> represent the mean of the differences from table 1</p>\n<p>(e.g. column 2-column 1)</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Condone an alternative hypothesis of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>:</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, provided it is consistent with their subsequent work (e.g. their “differences” are year 1 – year 2).</p>\n<p>Accept hypotheses communicated in words, e.g. “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>:</mo></math>there has been no change in the mean of the players’ averages”. The word “mean” must be seen in any word-based response.</p>\n<p>Allow <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>.</p>\n<p>Allow a compound null hypothesis (i.e. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>μ</mi><mi>d</mi></msub><mo>≤</mo><mn>0</mn></math> or equivalent).</p>\n<p>Condone <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>μ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> for null hypothesis and equivalent for alternative hypothesis.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22651845","referenceCode":"24M.3.AHL.TZ2.1di","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"State the null and alternative hypotheses for the test.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.18—T and Z test, type I and II errors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}